40
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:12,437
As if they'd all taken leave of their
senses.

41
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:16,993
For ten years the small kingdoms were
at war.

42
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:22,356
Peter grew into an upright young man.
But his father was losing his strenght,

43
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,079
grieving for the good wife he had lost.

44
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,635
Steward...

45
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:37,880
You maintained war
would make our fortune.

46
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,632
Where is that fortune?

47
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:43,269
To make it we'd have needed 5,000 ducats

48
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:46,272
for an army-to win!

49
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,999
Why did you make war then?

50
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:51,514
I keep you,
to keep track of these things!

51
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,591
It's no fun ruling.

52
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,432
I like hunting!

53
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:58,432
After your wars there isn't a partridge
in my woods.

54
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:01,478
If we set up an army.

55
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,120
I'd need 5,000.

56
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:07,636
You've gone mad.
Damn it, where are my...

57
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,678
Keys?

58
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,638
Keys!

59
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,751
Good morning.
- Good morning.

60
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,195
Don't you know
where my cash-box keys are?

61
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,713
Adela!
- No, Pappa.

62
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,751
Angelina?
- Oh, Pappa.

63
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:24,308
Where can they be?

64
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,428
Adela!

65
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,557
But this is where you usually put them!
- Here!

66
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,837
I never put it there.
- There?

67
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,678
Here!
- There!

68
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:41,554
That's all...

69
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,395
AII? ...our cash.
- You promised me a new dress!

70
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,956
The steward needs money a new army.
- 5,000.

71
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,315
Adela never moans about new dresses.

72
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:56,473
Because I give her mine
and then have nothing to wear.

73
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:59,279
Let go,
this is State money.

74
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:04,797
Don't cry, Angelina,

75
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:07,030
this dress is good enough for me.
- Shut up, you goose.

76
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,868
I'll never get married this way.

77
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:14,595
Must I do it all myself, you lazybones?

78
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:18,718
You're such a help, my boy.

79
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,996
Ah, the steward...

80
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:25,469
Go watch your pots.
- We are honoured.

81
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:29,236
Have you thought of getting married,
Dorothy?

82
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,071
The man in my heart

83
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,958
would hardly choose me.

84
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,954
How about Machal the miller?

85
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:39,995
Machal?

86
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:42,355
That old geezer?

87
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:46,797
I thought you were more cunning.
If a bright young woman married him

88
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:50,714
the mill could soon hers.

89
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,791
But he's got a son.

90
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,030
That can be arranged.

91
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,315
Where did that cat come from?

92
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,277
In the kitchen?

93
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:18,149
Good morning, neighbour!

94
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,311
Good morning.

95
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:23,831
Dear God, what a mess!
I was passing by,

96
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:26,480
something's burning,
would you like some help?

97
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,432
Thank you.

98
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:35,152
This is a woman's job.

99
00:06:57,840 --> 00:07:00,513
There, aren't they lovely.

100
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,636
Help yourselves!
There's lots!

101
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:10,397
In a matter of weeks -
they were married.

102
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:15,953
If an old man wants to play the fool,

103
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:18,829
he marries a young woman.

104
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:22,356
For this we'll buy the field by the
pond.

105
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:27,112
The mill's enough, Dorothy,
a field would mean more work still!

106
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:31,311
But Frankie, you're so strong!

107
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,995
Surely you don't feel old?

108
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:37,310
Of course not.

109
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,876
Mind you don't burn it.

110
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,594
Haven't you got a good wife?

111
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:48,832
I have.

112
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:52,478
Others would spend it all on clothes.

113
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,673
Why did you let the men go?

114
00:07:56,760 --> 00:08:00,833
Whoever heard of two men doing all
the work?

115
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:05,033
You do nothing but lazy around.
We have no money to waste!

116
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:11,399
Dad, say something!

117
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:17,509
Dorothy is right, Peter.
We'll manage.

118
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,719
Frankie!
There's a dance on tonight.

119
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,668
You haven't forgotten, have you?

120
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,910
But Dorothy, I'm...
- Or do I go by myself?

121
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,836
No, Dorothy, no.

122
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:06,913
And now a gavotte!

123
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,792
Let's sit his out.

124
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:11,189
D'you want me to dance
with someone else?

125
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,157
No.
- Well then!

126
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:27,711
Faster!

127
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,277
Frankie!

128
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:50,111
Poor unhappy me.
What'll I do without him?!

129
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,354
Once upon a time there was Hell.

130
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:49,588
There they had a pair of scales,
not to weigh people's pounds

131
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:53,237
but their sins.

132
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:56,275
There was no cheating it.

133
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:23,149
Stop!

134
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:30,238
Stand still and give me a report!

135
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:34,949
Your Majesty, King of the Darkness,
Lucifer XIV.

136
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,429
I bear fresh news of Dorothy Machal.

137
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:40,114
Wait!

138
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:43,795
Where is the Book of Sins?
- It should have been here!

139
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,439
Her cup of sins has overflowed.

140
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,476
Here's the Book.
- Scram!

141
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:04,357
Come here!

142
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,670
You left your post?!

143
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,671
The Bat has taken over!
- Quiet!

144
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:12,793
I thought...
- Silence!

145
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,991
Scram!

146
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:24,472
Dorothy Machal, page 1027,

147
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:26,949
line eight.
- I can see.

148
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,436
Line eight...

149
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:31,795
So I see.
I look-and see!

150
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,996
Yes, here.

151
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,075
You impertinent devil.

152
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:42,636
What do I see?

153
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,990
What do we see?

154
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:49,476
Stand still!
Don't move!

155
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:59,235
I said don't move!

156
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,198
That's my boot.

157
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:11,794
That was your boot.

158
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:16,791
A feather.
Where did it come from?

159
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,509
Come here, Cat!

160
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:23,315
Here, come on!

161
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,636
Let's see your teeth!

162
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:29,075
Teeth!

163
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,671
Your hands!

164
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:36,555
The other one!

165
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,391
It hurts!

166
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:42,429
All devils-line up!

167
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,311
No!

168
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,516
Come here!

169
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:11,473
A chicken!
All change back!

170
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:25,835
Your hand!
What is that?!

171
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:27,515
What is that?!

172
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,591
I was so terribly hungry!

173
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:33,992
I'll show you, wanting meat.

174
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:37,834
I hereby degrade you to rabbit!

175
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:44,632
That was one single feather!

176
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:48,833
Were it not for my intervention...

177
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:53,510
the Book of Sins'd have been destroyed!

178
00:15:57,840 --> 00:16:00,195
So was my advice good, Dorothy?

179
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,635
Very good.
Do help yourself,

180
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:05,598
we're not stingy like at the castle.

181
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:09,036
Yes.
How pretty you are today, Dorothy.

182
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,352
A young one.

183
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,756
Tender?

184
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:38,515
I hurried over
to tell you -

185
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,909
how sorry I am.

186
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:49,197
You didn't even know my father.

187
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:51,914
Go and mend the roof, it's leaking.

188
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,430
Did you hear me?

189
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:04,391
The lazy lout.

190
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:40,792
Get down at once!
Take that of the chimney!

191
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:44,111
I am mending the roof

192
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,191
as you told me to.

193
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:47,679
Did you hear me?

194
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:50,877
Climb down at once,
you young rascal!

195
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:53,117
At once!

196
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,235
You're right.

197
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,552
I'm going.

198
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,393
No.

199
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:06,517
You dropped something.

200
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:09,637
Help me, woman.
What is this?

201
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:11,073
It smells horrid.

202
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:14,311
Where're you going?
You haven't chopped the wood yet!

203
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,152
Let the steward chop it for you!

204
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:19,118
I'll be back when you're gone!

205
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,670
This will cost you dear!

206
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:27,829
You lot her cheat you out of everything?

207
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:30,715
Where's your common sense?

208
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,951
I didn't leave everything.
Look!

209
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:41,269
My mother's.
The ring I'll give my bride one day.

210
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:53,192
Peek-a-boo!
I've got the warrant for arrest

211
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:58,199
for that stepson of yours.

212
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,076
When his Majesty signs it

213
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:04,869
the mill will soon be ours.
I mean yours.

214
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:10,954
A life sentence.
- A life sentence.

215
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:13,956
Good!
- Isn't it?

216
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:16,838
But it'll cost something.

217
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:25,070
No, no.

218
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,034
There was no need for that.
Put you'll need some for his Majesty,

219
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:30,680
He's so money-minded.

220
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:36,231
Angeline!

221
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:40,438
Come on!

222
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,875
Wait!

223
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,911
Wait for me!

224
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,912
Caught you!

225
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:56,709
Look what you've done!
Torn my only dress!

226
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,519
I'm sorry, Angelina.
Forgive me.

227
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,795
Come on!
- We can darn it!

228
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:03,757
No we can't.

229
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:07,629
I am willing to ignore

230
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,950
that he wanted to kill me,

231
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:14,318
but he robbed his mother,
that sadly berieved widow,

232
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:18,190
and he up and left her

233
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:19,838
with the whole mill to look after!

234
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,753
What do I do?
I didn't bring up her son!

235
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:25,195
No, your Majesty!

236
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:27,794
You could jail him.

237
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:31,555
He is an incredibly dangerous man.

238
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,437
Look, come back some other time.

239
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:36,240
I'm busy right now.

240
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,914
So he's a naughty boy?

241
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,792
I'm a helpless woman,

242
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,758
I'm afraid of him!

243
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:02,957
You're telling me,
children are a worry.

244
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,798
Yes.

245
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:09,279
Here.

246
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:11,794
Pappa, now you'll admit

247
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,553
that I need a new dress!

248
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:16,437
Here.

249
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,158
What has Petr Machal done,
that you want him jailed?

250
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,595
Children...
- May I?

251
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:24,552
There.

252
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:28,599
Would your Majesty take up the pen

253
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:34,070
and sign here, please.

254
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:36,550
Sign up, Pappa!

255
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:37,914
After you've ascertained

256
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:41,151
who's in the right!
- Oh, come on.

257
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,999
Right indeed.

258
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:53,040
Yes.

259
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,036
Joseph the Handsome.

260
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,070
I didn't hear you say good day.

261
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:13,150
On his Majesty's decision
you are under arrest.

262
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,478
No.

263
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,636
Arrested?
Why?

264
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,560
They'll explain at the castle.

265
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,958
Come on!

266
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:40,550
Go away!

267
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:53,796
Come on up!

268
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:56,440
You'll pay for this.

269
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:59,114
My best to his Majesty.

270
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:04,193
You must run.

271
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:06,999
Why?
I haven't done anything.

272
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:11,039
How can you rebel against the masters?
You must always stay in their good books

273
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:13,509
if you want to live in contentment.

274
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:16,797
I want to live in contentment, Grandma.
But here.

275
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:29,154
What's this?
Open the door!

276
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:38,840
