00:50:42,760 --> 00:50:44,557
Wait.

550
00:50:44,960 --> 00:50:46,996
Down!
Up!

551
00:50:48,160 --> 00:50:50,151
Down!
Up!

552
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:57,437
Arms at the ready!

553
00:51:01,400 --> 00:51:03,470
That's rebellion!
Throw your weapon down!

554
00:51:05,840 --> 00:51:07,876
What's that?

555
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:10,633
Machal, back in line!
What did I say?

556
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:16,755
Get back, Machal!

557
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:20,310
20 days' jail
and 50 lashings!

558
00:51:21,760 --> 00:51:24,399
Come back!

559
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:27,032
Did you see that?

560
00:51:27,120 --> 00:51:29,714
Peter must have a good heart.

561
00:51:29,800 --> 00:51:32,951
You and your Peter.

562
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:36,072
Mine?

563
00:51:36,200 --> 00:51:38,794
You know he wants you.
And you?

564
00:51:39,560 --> 00:51:43,030
Exactly.
Men need tricking, you silly.

565
00:51:50,560 --> 00:51:52,869
50 lashings.

566
00:51:53,400 --> 00:51:55,231
They shout at you all day
make you roll in the mud.

567
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:59,836
And all because of that woman.

568
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:03,230
Surely you're not in love?

569
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:05,072
No fear.

570
00:52:05,160 --> 00:52:08,596
I was to bring a bad widow to Hell.

571
00:52:09,960 --> 00:52:13,157
Was it Dorothy Machal by any chance?

572
00:52:15,800 --> 00:52:17,711
How do you know?

573
00:52:18,560 --> 00:52:20,278
If anybody I know deserves hell,

574
00:52:20,360 --> 00:52:23,591
it's my stepmother.

575
00:52:26,360 --> 00:52:29,158
So you are Peter?

576
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:32,228
And you really are a devil.

577
00:52:32,720 --> 00:52:35,234
I should say!

578
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:41,436
Oh, but I'm not any more.
I'd have to get my wolf's tail back.

579
00:52:43,400 --> 00:52:45,311
A wolf's tail?

580
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:50,394
I can't go back to hell till I have it.

581
00:52:51,000 --> 00:52:53,389
What do you mean, a wolf's tail?

582
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:57,358
I can't change back without it.

583
00:52:59,360 --> 00:53:01,476
I don't get it.

584
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:06,474
Go clean out the stables.

585
00:53:24,040 --> 00:53:27,430
Doesn't Princess Angelina

586
00:53:27,520 --> 00:53:29,397
Iook lovely?

587
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:33,356
Our cash-box is empty,
the ceiling's coming down

588
00:53:33,600 --> 00:53:36,876
and we hold balls for borrowed money.

589
00:53:37,160 --> 00:53:39,196
Curtsy, Angelina!

590
00:53:39,280 --> 00:53:41,475
To the green one.

591
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:43,671
It's all arranged.

592
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:45,671
Angelina, Curtsy.

593
00:53:45,760 --> 00:53:49,116
Angelina will marry richest suitor,

594
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:52,790
we'll pay our debts and have some over.

595
00:53:53,400 --> 00:53:56,119
Do you like any of them?

596
00:53:58,200 --> 00:54:00,509
Whom do you like?

597
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:03,513
Who is the richest?

598
00:54:03,640 --> 00:54:06,279
She says who is the richest?

599
00:54:06,360 --> 00:54:08,874
Well, who is the richest?
- Who is??

600
00:54:08,960 --> 00:54:11,918
quietly.
I'll find out.

601
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:17,276
Can it be a dead wolf's tail?

602
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:21,316
Sure,
how'd you out it off a live one?

603
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:27,439
I know of one.
But how to got out of the barracks.

604
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:29,632
Wait!

605
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:34,714
Ah, for our lovely pub
ah, for their lovely grub,

606
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:40,312
the soup is so hot

607
00:54:40,640 --> 00:54:43,074
the boor is with froth!

608
00:54:56,680 --> 00:54:58,636
What's happening?

609
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:00,791
What's should be?

610
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:02,518
Nothing?
- Nothing.

611
00:55:03,160 --> 00:55:05,151
Sure?
- Sure.

612
00:55:27,360 --> 00:55:30,238
I know now who's the richest.

613
00:55:30,320 --> 00:55:33,039
I've investigated.

614
00:55:33,240 --> 00:55:37,791
According to ancient custom
the Princess will throw a golden apple,

615
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:42,149
the man it stops by will become
her husband.

616
00:55:43,480 --> 00:55:47,234
But that's not gold.

617
00:55:48,160 --> 00:55:49,434
No, I shall gold it.

618
00:55:49,520 --> 00:55:52,159
What if it rolls some Pauper?

619
00:55:52,240 --> 00:55:54,390
Yes.
The ball is actually made of iron.

620
00:55:55,720 --> 00:55:58,109
And this stone will make it stop

621
00:55:58,200 --> 00:56:01,715
by the richest of the suitors.

622
00:56:03,320 --> 00:56:06,278
Try pulling it away.

623
00:56:06,360 --> 00:56:08,794
I can't.

624
00:56:09,720 --> 00:56:11,790
I'll do it.

625
00:56:13,840 --> 00:56:16,479
What is this stone?

626
00:56:16,560 --> 00:56:20,917
It comes from Magnet Mountain

627
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:23,116
and attracts all iron objects.

628
00:56:24,160 --> 00:56:27,709
I did say all iron objects.

629
00:57:12,840 --> 00:57:14,910
Yes, but...

630
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:17,434
I'd prefer...

631
00:57:17,520 --> 00:57:20,114
The army is important,

632
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:23,357
believe me.

633
00:58:07,680 --> 00:58:10,752
Hello, officer!
What are you doing here?

634
00:58:13,480 --> 00:58:16,358
How lovely you look, Princess.

635
00:58:16,440 --> 00:58:18,954
And gallant, too.

636
00:58:19,040 --> 00:58:21,952
But you haven't asked me dance yet!

637
00:58:22,400 --> 00:58:25,836
Permit me to rectify my mistake.

638
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:35,352
For so long I've been wanting...
- Long?

639
00:58:35,440 --> 00:58:37,670
I don't know you, you must be new.

640
00:58:37,760 --> 00:58:39,910
Good evening, Peter.
- Good evening.

641
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:43,037
That's Machal, the young miller.

642
00:58:43,560 --> 00:58:47,189
Where did you steal the uniform?
How dare you?

643
00:58:48,120 --> 00:58:49,269
Guards!

644
00:58:49,360 --> 00:58:51,555
Wait, Angelina!

645
00:58:51,640 --> 00:58:53,995
Guards!

646
00:58:55,080 --> 00:58:57,355
I only wanted to see you.

647
00:58:57,440 --> 00:58:59,908
Catch him!

648
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:02,673
Hurry up!
Throw him in prison!

649
00:59:19,200 --> 00:59:21,589
Peter!
Hide in here!

650
00:59:26,160 --> 00:59:28,116
He ran this way!

651
00:59:31,120 --> 00:59:32,758
Come on!

652
00:59:37,640 --> 00:59:40,438
Thank you, Princess.
- Run!

653
00:59:44,080 --> 00:59:47,436
Prince, do you want our Princess?

654
00:59:51,320 --> 00:59:54,073
I'd give anything...

655
01:00:00,720 --> 01:00:04,110
Put this in your shoe and she is yours.

656
01:00:05,800 --> 01:00:09,554
According to ancient custom
the Princess's husband

657
01:00:13,080 --> 01:00:16,516
will be chosen...
justly... by this golden apple.

658
01:00:20,320 --> 01:00:22,629
He to whom it rolls will have her.

659
01:00:23,760 --> 01:00:26,433
As his wife!

660
01:00:26,640 --> 01:00:28,631
As his wife.

661
01:00:37,400 --> 01:00:39,868
The apple.
Roll it towards the left.

662
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:57,036
No!

663
01:00:58,840 --> 01:01:00,751
Help!

664
01:01:02,800 --> 01:01:04,756
Pappa!

665
01:01:07,680 --> 01:01:11,036
I'll tell my Pappa and
he'll declare war!

666
01:01:11,120 --> 01:01:13,588
Congratulations, you won.

667
01:01:13,680 --> 01:01:17,070
My Pappa will make war on you.
Carry him away.

668
01:01:22,280 --> 01:01:25,113
Pappa'll make war!

669
01:01:34,840 --> 01:01:37,957
Take this thing out of my shoe!

670
01:01:38,760 --> 01:01:41,672
What thing?

671
01:01:41,760 --> 01:01:43,432
We've been cheated!

672
01:01:43,520 --> 01:01:46,239
Take my shoe off!

673
01:01:46,560 --> 01:01:48,232
We want the money we lent you!

674
01:01:48,320 --> 01:01:50,356
We've been tricked!
- Silence!

675
01:01:50,440 --> 01:01:53,432
We'll declare war together!

676
01:01:54,480 --> 01:01:57,950
Take my shoe off!
My Pappa'll make war on you!

677
01:01:59,920 --> 01:02:01,911
Sure.

678
01:02:03,160 --> 01:02:05,310
What will we do?

679
01:02:08,480 --> 01:02:11,119
Luckily we have a strong army.

680
01:02:12,880 --> 01:02:15,838
There's a parade tomorrow.

681
01:02:15,920 --> 01:02:17,717
What?
- A parade.

682
01:02:18,400 --> 01:02:20,834
We have a parade?

683
01:02:20,920 --> 01:02:22,638
Come and see.
- I'll come.

684
01:02:24,880 --> 01:02:28,668
Action stations!

685
01:02:29,360 --> 01:02:33,148
Dammit-all-to-hell
I said action stations!

686
01:02:34,320 --> 01:02:36,151
Sound the alarm!

687
01:02:36,720 --> 01:02:38,756
Attention!
Where is your uniform, you stupid?

688
01:02:43,360 --> 01:02:45,112
Attention!

689
01:02:46,000 --> 01:02:48,036
Attention!
Attention!

690
01:03:27,280 --> 01:03:29,032
This way.

691
01:03:30,280 --> 01:03:32,669
Excuse me, where's the door.

692
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:05,592
Fire!

693
01:04:15,200 --> 01:04:16,838
Come!

694
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:29,157
My dress!

695
01:04:48,360 --> 01:04:51,989
Corporal!
Is this what you call a strong army?

696
01:05:05,160 --> 01:05:07,037
Catch him!

697
01:05:08,800 --> 01:05:10,995
Bring my horse!

698
01:05:21,040 --> 01:05:23,634
Backwards again!

699
01:05:24,080 --> 01:05:26,071
What?
- Turn me round!

700
01:05:26,160 --> 01:05:29,311
Turn the horse round!
- Not the horse, me!

701
01:05:56,080 --> 01:05:57,832
Wait.

702
01:06:00,880 --> 01:06:02,598
Now.

703
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:13,550
Dorothy!
Dorothy!

704
01:06:30,840 --> 01:06:33,149
Let me go!

705
01:06:36,000 --> 01:06:38,150
Leave me alone!
Help!

706
01:06:39,680 --> 01:06:41,511
Help!
No!

707
01:06:54,520 --> 01:06:56,875
Follow them!
Encircle them!

708
01:06:57,840 --> 01:07:00,195
quickly!

709
01:07:02,320 --> 01:07:04,709
Everybody here!

710
01:07:05,600 --> 01:07:07,591
Help!

711
01:07:09,600 --> 01:07:11,318
Peter!

712
01:07:12,440 --> 01:07:14,590
Give it to me.

713
01:07:14,680 --> 01:07:16,636
Come on, Peter!

714
01:07:19,520 --> 01:07:21,590
Follow them quickly!

715
01:07:21,800 --> 01:07:23,995
We must get them!

716
01:07:26,320 --> 01:07:28,072
How's that?

717
01:07:28,160 --> 01:07:31,914
This doesn't load anywhere.
Dammit-all-to-hell!

718
01:07:32,640 --> 01:07:35,791
You're ready for the gallows, Machal!

719
01:07:38,120 --> 01:07:41,635
Hell's bells and cocker shells!

720
01:07:44,080 --> 01:07:46,833
The gallows for you!

721
01:07:48,920 --> 01:07:51,309
I snapped my sword!

722
01:07:53,160 --> 01:07:55,833
My dear boy!

723
01:07:55,920 --> 01:07:58,115
How happy I am to see you.

724
01:08:15,840 --> 01:08:18,070
Good, she's sinking!

725
01:08:26,320 --> 01:08:28,675
She's ours!

726
01:08:31,760 --> 01:08:33,716
Take her!

727
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:38,950
She broke our scales.

728
01:08:39,040 --> 01:08:40,712
Come here.

729
01:08:41,320 --> 01:08:43,675
What do we do with him?

730
01:08:43,920 --> 01:08:47,959
Leave me here for a few days.
They want to hang me.

731
01:08:49,080 --> 01:08:51,071
Let go!

732
01:08:51,760 --> 01:08:54,274
Take your hands away you hairy monster!

733
01:08:54,360 --> 01:08:56,510
Help!

734
01:08:56,640 --> 01:08:58,790
Let me go!

735
01:08:59,080 --> 01:09:01,469
Don't touch me!

736
01:09:01,560 --> 01:09:03,710
No,
help!

737
01:09:03,800 --> 01:09:06,234
Help!
Help!

738
01:09:21,000 --> 01:09:24,037
This is an ultimatum!
The ceiling's coming down.

739
01:09:27,280 --> 01:09:30,556
Either I return their money within
the month

740
01:09:30,640 --> 01:09:34,315
or they'll declare war.

741
01:09:35,960 --> 01:09:38,349
Signed-all nine kingdoms.

742
01:09:40,400 --> 01:09:43,437
Where am I to find the money?

743
01:09:47,280 --> 01:09:49,840
How about selling the castle?

744
01:09:50,040 --> 01:09:53,396
Are you mad?
Sell the roof over my head?

745
01:09:55,480 --> 01:09:58,995
Actually, who'd buy the old ruin.

746
01:10:01,040 --> 01:10:04,510
This castle was built
in the 12th century by my ancestors,

747
01:10:05,240 --> 01:10:09,199
Ferdinand the Handsome and Josephine
the Mad.

748
01:10:12,160 --> 01:10:16,278
Maybe I'd buy it off you,

749
01:10:21,800 --> 01:10:24,234
to do you a favour.

750
01:10:29,120 --> 01:10:32,590
The water strokes the pebbles

751
01:10:38,760 --> 01:10:42,309
tenderly and softly
that is love.

752
01:10:49,520 --> 01:10:53,069
Tenderly and softly
that is love.

753
01:11:01,960 --> 01:11:06,875
Peter, dearest Peter,

754
01:11:10,640 --> 01:11:13,200
who'll tell you that we two

755
01:11:13,680 --> 01:11:16,558
are made for each other.

756
01:11:27,120 --> 01:11:28,951
Get up!

757
01:11:29,600 --> 01:11:31,795
The Devil never sleeps!

758
01:11:32,080 --> 01:11:34,799
He did all this in a few days.

759
01:11:34,880 --> 01:11:37,678
Leave that be and come here!

760
01:11:37,760 --> 01:11:41,514
What do you think you're doing?
All this work down here?!

761
01:11:41,600 --> 01:11:42,919
You'll spoil our reputation!

762
01:11:43,000 --> 01:11:46,515
Make three wishes
and back to Earth with you!

763
01:11:47,160 --> 01:11:50,357
One wish -
take me back home.

764
01:11:51,880 --> 01:11:54,553
Of course, I will.
But what else?

765
01:11:54,960 --> 01:11:57,030
Wait a minute.

766
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:08,832
Ask for this.

767
01:12:08,920 --> 01:12:11,514
Such a scruffy old coat?
- It's magic.

768
01:12:12,160 --> 01:12:15,232
He who wears it finds a ducat

769
01:12:15,320 --> 01:12:17,436
in his pocket every time.

770
01:12:18,520 --> 01:12:20,750
What is your wish?

771
01:12:20,840 --> 01:12:22,876
To go back to Earth

772
01:12:22,960 --> 01:12:25,713
to fetch the Corporal!

773
01:12:25,800 --> 01:12:28,030
I'm coming with you.

774
01:12:28,120 --> 01:12:31,476
All right.
You may take the coat.

775
01:12:35,240 --> 01:12:37,276
And your grandmother.

776
01:12:37,880 --> 01:12:41,031
I'll let Johnny go under the condition

777
01:12:41,680 --> 01:12:45,832
that he brings the Corporal and
the Steward.

778
01:12:49,240 --> 01:12:52,198
All right.
But won't they hang me?

779
01:12:54,600 --> 01:12:57,876
With that coat on you are protected.

780
01:12:57,960 --> 01:13:00,030
Put it on!

781
01:13:02,240 --> 01:13:04,310
But don't forget -

782
01:13:04,400 --> 01:13:07,870
when you take it off you lose all
powers.

783
01:13:13,160 --> 01:13:15,276
May we go?

784
01:13:16,040 --> 01:13:18,315
Let's see you.
Yes, you may!

785
01:13:23,040 --> 01:13:26,077
Whom do we fetch first,
the Steward or the Corporal?

786
01:13:26,160 --> 01:13:28,674
I'm going home to bake some cakes.

787
01:13:29,640 --> 01:13:32,950
We're going to the pub.

788
01:13:33,040 --> 01:13:34,598
Not even Lucifer
will get me to the pub.

789
01:13:34,680 --> 01:13:37,558
That's where all my troubles began!

790
01:13:37,640 --> 01:13:39,471
So I'll make the sacrifice and go.

791
01:13:39,560 --> 01:13:42,438
You keep watch outside.
- You're great.

792
01:13:42,520 --> 01:13:44,397
The devil!
The devil!

793
01:13:44,680 --> 01:13:46,352
The devil!

794
01:13:47,080 --> 01:13:49,435
How did they recognize you?
Me? Look at yourself!

795
01:14:01,160 --> 01:14:02,912
Potato soup.

796
01:14:03,000 --> 01:14:04,638
A full plate, please!

797
01:14:04,720 --> 01:14:07,075
Pork with sauerkraut.
- Yes, Sir.

798
01:14:08,360 --> 01:14:10,157
Goulash.

799
01:14:10,360 --> 01:14:12,157
With bread.

800
01:14:12,240 --> 01:14:14,595
And cream-cheese dumplings.

801
01:14:15,800 --> 01:14:18,109
Right,
but can you pay?

802
01:14:30,200 --> 01:14:33,431
Your servant, Milord -
at first sight I thought...

803
01:14:34,600 --> 01:14:37,831
that you're...

804
01:14:38,280 --> 01:14:40,589
What?

805
01:14:41,120 --> 01:14:42,951
The devil!

806
01:14:43,120 --> 01:14:45,076
Oh no.

807
01:14:45,160 --> 01:14:47,720
I'm no devil.
I only look that way.

808
01:14:47,800 --> 01:14:50,917
Take a seat,
it won't be long.

809
01:15:27,720 --> 01:15:29,995
Take them.
They're yours.

810
01:15:55,800 --> 01:15:57,836
Lots of money you say?

811
01:15:57,920 --> 01:16:01,276
Must be a foreigner.

812
01:16:01,640 --> 01:16:04,108
He's throwing ducats around.

813
01:16:04,320 --> 01:16:06,117
Ducats?

814
01:16:06,200 --> 01:16:08,634
He hands out as many as they ask for.

815
01:16:08,720 --> 01:16:11,029
But Angelina.
- He must be mad.

816
01:16:11,840 --> 01:16:15,071
See?
- Dress up as a pauper and go!

817
01:16:15,520 --> 01:16:18,876
We can't miss such a chance!

818
01:16:21,320 --> 01:16:23,311
82
- 82, thank you.

819
01:16:24,400 --> 01:16:28,075
83
- 83, thank you.

820
01:16:28,160 --> 01:16:31,038
84
- 84, thank you.

821
01:16:31,120 --> 01:16:32,792
Come in!

822
01:16:35,080 --> 01:16:37,116
Excuse me.

823
01:16:44,440 --> 01:16:46,510
That's the Steward, you know!

824
01:16:46,880 --> 01:16:49,713
I know.
I'll knock his feathered hat off.

825
01:16:49,800 --> 01:16:51,916
And I'll catch him.

826
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:57,033
Where were we?
- 80

827
01:16:59,840 --> 01:17:02,638
81
- 81

828
01:17:02,880 --> 01:17:05,474
82
- 82

829
01:17:06,240 --> 01:17:08,834
83
- 83

830
01:17:10,120 --> 01:17:12,190
84

831
01:17:13,360 --> 01:17:15,715
How dare you?

832
01:17:30,960 --> 01:17:34,635
See this feather?
I have two, just in case!

833
01:17:42,000 --> 01:17:45,834
Noble foreigner, you won't believe me

834
01:17:46,040 --> 01:17:50,033
but I'm the poorest man around.

835
01:17:50,480 --> 01:17:53,278
They all cheat me,
my children, the steward...

836
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:57,872
All I have but debts.

837
01:17:58,040 --> 01:18:00,759
What would you like, your Majesty?

838
01:18:00,920 --> 01:18:02,672
How can you know I'm...

839
01:18:04,920 --> 01:18:07,753
Let's not play hide and seek.

840
01:18:07,840 --> 01:18:10,308
How much do you need?

841
01:18:11,680 --> 01:18:13,989
20,000 ducats.

842
01:18:20,520 --> 01:18:22,909
All right,

843
01:18:23,320 --> 01:18:27,074
but if you give me your daughter in
marriage.

844
01:18:31,320 --> 01:18:33,390
30.000

845
01:18:38,720 --> 01:18:41,188
I know it's a lot.

846
01:18:41,280 --> 01:18:43,271
I don't understand.

847
01:18:43,360 --> 01:18:46,477
I'm not scared, but I need help.

848
01:18:46,560 --> 01:18:48,073
Help?

849
01:18:48,160 --> 01:18:51,391
I have the feeling the devil
is after me.

850
01:18:53,040 --> 01:18:54,553
The devil...

851
01:18:54,640 --> 01:18:56,551
The devil.

852
01:19:03,080 --> 01:19:05,719
I'll think of something.

853
01:19:05,880 --> 01:19:07,677
Don't bother,

854
01:19:07,760 --> 01:19:10,069
I've done that myself.

855
01:19:10,160 --> 01:19:13,516
But I need a certain bunch of keys.

856
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:17,036
Keys?

857
01:19:20,920 --> 01:19:23,354
I know the whereabouts of the steward
and corporal.

858
01:19:23,760 --> 01:19:25,751
I heard them make arrangements.

859
01:19:25,840 --> 01:19:27,478
But they've still got the feather.

860
01:19:27,560 --> 01:19:29,437
Never mind.

861
01:19:29,840 --> 01:19:32,718
Is the look dependable?

862
01:19:32,800 --> 01:19:36,156
Sure,
it can be unlocked only from outside

863
01:19:37,200 --> 01:19:40,556
and there stand the guards.
We are absolutely safe.

864
01:20:12,360 --> 01:20:14,874
Come on, you...

865
01:20:35,560 --> 01:20:37,516
Come here.

866
01:20:46,880 --> 01:20:50,589
Come, little orphan,
join the others.

867
01:20:57,040 --> 01:21:00,112
Here I am.
High time, too.

868
01:21:01,120 --> 01:21:03,236
Corporal!

869
01:21:11,400 --> 01:21:13,197
quickly.

870
01:21:16,880 --> 01:21:19,030
Sound the alarm!
Sound the alarm!

871
01:21:19,480 --> 01:21:21,630
Which way?

872
01:21:26,760 --> 01:21:28,671
What a lot of money!

873
01:21:28,760 --> 01:21:31,274
I'll have some.

874
01:21:34,400 --> 01:21:36,470
Help!

875
01:21:50,480 --> 01:21:52,277
Where are they?

876
01:22:02,440 --> 01:22:04,510
Soldiers, attention!

877
01:22:08,000 --> 01:22:09,956
There they are!

878
01:22:10,040 --> 01:22:12,349
Not there, this way.

879
01:22:13,240 --> 01:22:15,754
The secret passage to the castle!

880
01:22:17,320 --> 01:22:19,788
I'll help you.

881
01:22:25,800 --> 01:22:27,631
This way?
Run!

882
01:22:43,480 --> 01:22:45,516
Climb out!

883
01:22:48,680 --> 01:22:52,309
No feathers.
- On our hats!

884
01:22:52,400 --> 01:22:54,550
Back to the chest!

885
01:22:57,720 --> 01:22:59,676
quickly!
- This way!

886
01:23:00,240 --> 01:23:02,390
I want to...

887
01:23:21,640 --> 01:23:23,835
Wait here...

888
01:23:25,600 --> 01:23:27,556
But Pappa...
- Who are you?

889
01:23:31,520 --> 01:23:33,636
What are you doing here?

890
01:23:34,880 --> 01:23:36,632
Come on!

891
01:23:43,040 --> 01:23:45,395
Here we're safe.

892
01:23:45,880 --> 01:23:48,952
And now we can disappear.

893
01:23:51,520 --> 01:23:55,115
We're wasted in this stupid kingdom.

894
01:24:06,240 --> 01:24:08,310
Thank you, Peter!

895
01:24:08,520 --> 01:24:10,988
You'll have to marry him,
or he won't give us the money!

896
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:13,469
When he spruces up a bit...

897
01:24:13,560 --> 01:24:17,155
I'm doing no such thing.
The Princess must marry me as I am.

898
01:24:18,000 --> 01:24:21,037
I'll never marry such an eyesore!

899
01:24:21,120 --> 01:24:22,838
Never!

900
01:24:22,960 --> 01:24:25,474
Our debts!
Don't offend him.

901
01:24:25,560 --> 01:24:27,949
I couldn't stand people seeing me
with such a fright!

902
01:24:28,040 --> 01:24:31,794
As you like.
Goodbye.

903
01:24:33,360 --> 01:24:35,828
Please, dear children!

904
01:24:36,240 --> 01:24:39,118
There'd be war!

905
01:24:39,440 --> 01:24:42,398
Get her to marry him, Pappa!

906
01:24:47,440 --> 01:24:49,829
I'll keep my word.

907
01:24:51,360 --> 01:24:54,033
My daughter will marry you.

908
01:24:55,560 --> 01:24:59,348
She will sacrifice herself
for the Kingdom, for the family.

909
01:25:04,240 --> 01:25:06,231
Au revoir.

910
01:25:08,040 --> 01:25:09,792
Wait!

911
01:25:12,880 --> 01:25:14,871
Poor little girl.

912
01:25:14,960 --> 01:25:17,235
She'll get used to him.

913
01:25:17,760 --> 01:25:22,197
One for us,
one for his Majesty.

914
01:25:26,160 --> 01:25:29,118
One for us,
one for his Majesty.

915
01:25:37,720 --> 01:25:40,632
Pull out another, Peter.

916
01:25:40,720 --> 01:25:43,188
You'll need to renovate the mill.

917
01:25:43,320 --> 01:25:46,471
One for us,
and one for us too.

918
01:25:52,800 --> 01:25:55,917
And one each for luck.

919
01:26:00,320 --> 01:26:03,198
Tomorrow we go to the castle.

920
01:26:03,400 --> 01:26:05,630
I'm getting married.

921
01:26:14,080 --> 01:26:16,469
Why are you doing that?

922
01:26:23,560 --> 01:26:25,915
Thank you, Lucifer!

923
01:26:58,040 --> 01:26:59,917
Who is it?
- Wait.

924
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:02,830
Yes, they're real.

925
01:27:03,040 --> 01:27:05,952
I have come for my bride.

926
01:27:07,240 --> 01:27:09,674
I'm marrying this one!

927
01:27:10,960 --> 01:27:14,794
When I asked for your daughter,
I meant Adela.

928
01:27:15,120 --> 01:27:16,997
This one?!

929
01:27:17,160 --> 01:27:19,594
She's the one I'll marry.

930
01:27:20,120 --> 01:27:23,669
Dear children.
I'll stay on the shelf?!

931
01:27:23,920 --> 01:27:27,390
I'll think of something.

932
01:27:28,960 --> 01:27:31,349
I want a husband now!

933
01:27:58,240 --> 01:28:00,390
It's not fair!

934
01:28:00,480 --> 01:28:03,040
Angelina, please?
- Excuse me.

935
01:28:04,040 --> 01:28:06,031
May I have the pleasure?

936
01:28:07,400 --> 01:28:09,231
With your permission.

937
01:28:09,880 --> 01:28:12,553
Yes.

938
01:28:13,720 --> 01:28:17,110
Angelina, a partner for you.

939
01:28:18,280 --> 01:28:20,714
Interesting, passionate.

940
01:28:27,920 --> 01:28:31,754
A good thing you didn't marry
that miller.

941
01:28:31,840 --> 01:28:35,310
How about marrying a Prince?

942
01:28:36,280 --> 01:28:38,748
Even the Prince of Hell?

943
01:28:38,840 --> 01:28:41,991
Of course.
I don't believe in hell, you see.

944
01:28:42,320 --> 01:28:44,675
In that case...

945
01:28:46,480 --> 01:28:48,789
Lots of happiness.

946
01:28:49,080 --> 01:28:50,513
Johnny!

947
01:28:50,600 --> 01:28:52,318
Johnny!

948
01:28:53,560 --> 01:28:56,438
But that's...
- She'll be fine.

949
01:28:56,640 --> 01:28:58,358
Johnny!

950
01:28:58,800 --> 01:29:00,711
I've got to go.

951
01:29:00,800 --> 01:29:02,552
But...

952
01:29:10,800 --> 01:29:12,518
Johnny!

953
01:29:16,680 --> 01:29:18,398
Peter!

954
01:29:31,800 --> 01:29:35,429
Hell may exist or not,
but it was a good idea.

955
01:29:36,760 --> 01:29:39,558
If we look around us we see

956
01:29:39,640 --> 01:29:43,235
that many people would be in need of it.

957
01:29:44,600 --> 01:29:47,831
It isn't a good thing for people
to think

958
01:29:47,920 --> 01:29:50,593
that evil can go unpunished.

959
01:29:57,120 --> 01:29:59,315
I'm your love,

960
01:30:02,160 --> 01:30:04,310
you are my love, too.

961
01:30:06,640 --> 01:30:09,074
Why should we stay...

962
01:30:09,360 --> 01:30:12,158
...why should we stay alone.

963
01:30:20,360 --> 01:30:23,158
THE END

